<caption>Finite-length signals (<m:math>
  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
  <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
  <m:mi>t</m:mi>
  <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
</m:math>
 above) or periodic signals (<m:math>
  <m:msub>
    <m:mi>x</m:mi>
    <m:mi>p</m:mi>
  </m:msub>
  <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
  <m:mi>t</m:mi>
  <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
</m:math>
) can be represented as a weighted sum of complex sinusoids <m:math>
  <m:msub>
    <m:mi>c</m:mi>
