      <m:mi>n</m:mi>
      <m:mi>t</m:mi>
    </m:mrow>
  </m:msup>
</m:math>
.</caption></figure><para id="eip-73">Also recall the formula for a signal's representation with CTFS coefficients, letting <m:math>
  <m:msub>
    <m:mi>ω</m:mi>
    <m:mn>0</m:mn>
  </m:msub>
  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
