</m:math>
<newline/>
So, then, as shown in <link target-id="sampledctft"/>, a CTFS of a finite-length signal is actually just a sampled version of a CTFT for the same signal (though zero-padded to be infinite length). Every <m:math>
  <m:msub>
    <m:mi>c</m:mi>
    <m:mi>n</m:mi>
  </m:msub>
</m:math>
 is simply the value of the CTFT at location <m:math>
  <m:mi>n</m:mi>
  <m:msub>
    <m:mi>ω</m:mi>
    <m:mn>0</m:mn>
  </m:msub>
</m:math>.</para><figure id="sampledctft" orient="vertical"><subfigure id="sampledctfts1">
    <media id="sampledctftm1" alt="">
       <image mime-type="" src="../../media/i2_3.png"/>
